               <msContents>
                  <summary>Psalter, with three illuminations, ornate harags, and the Scholars Edition of the Song of Songs</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from="3r" to="137v" facs="003"/><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2701Dawit">Psalter</title>
                    <textLang mainLang="gez">Gǝ'ǝz</textLang>

                    <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.1"><locus from="3r" to="107v" facs="003"/><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur">Mazmura Dāwit</title>
                      <note><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps118Spiritual">Mazmura Dāwit, Psalm 118 including the Spritual Meaning of the Hebrew Letters</ref> in the new common system</note>
                      <note><ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps151">Mazmura Dāwit, Psalmus 151</ref> has all of the four plusses that make up the long version</note>
                    </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.2"><locus from="108r" to="119v" facs="108"/><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1828Mahale">Book of Odes</title>
                    <note>The superscription to the fourth biblical canticle, <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2257salota#Hannah">The Prayer of Hannah, mother of Samuel the Prophet,  Hannah</ref>, is <q>“Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel, prophet.”</q></note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.3"><locus from="119v" to="125v" facs="120"/><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2362Songof">Song of Songs</title>
                    <note>Common edition in the base hand; strophes of the scholars’ edition have been added interlinearly</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.4"><locus from="126r" to="134v" facs="126"/><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2509Weddas">Wǝddāse Māryām</title>
                    <note>Arranged for the days of the week, beginning on Monday and culminating on Sunday</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1.5"><locus from="134v" to="137v" facs="135"/><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1113Anqasa">ʾAnqaṣa bǝrhān</title></msItem>
              </msItem>


