                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word for God is systematically rubricated</desc>
                  <desc><title type="complete" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps150">Mazmura Dāwit, Psalmus 150</title> and <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1566hababa#ThreeYouths3">Third Song of the Three Youths in the Furnace,  ThreeYouths3</ref> employ columetric rubrication</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#1v" facs="002"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4306GabraMa">Gabra Manfas Qǝddus</persName>, in full color</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#2r" facs="002"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9162TaklaHa">Takla Hāymānot</persName>, in full color</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3"><locus target="#2v" facs="003"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1066DavidHarp">David Playing the Harp</ref>, in full color</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                      <locus target="#3r #38r #73v #108r #126r" facs="003 038 074 108 126"/>
                      <desc>
                      The harag on <locus target="#3r #38r #73v #108r" facs="003 038 074 108"/> and  (and elsewhere) spans the top and goes all the way down both sides.
                      The harag on <locus target="#126r" facs="126"/>, where the Praises of Mary begins in two columns, also has the harag in the middle margin
                      </desc>
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#56r" facs="056"/>
                    <desc>
                    The midpoint of the Psalms is marked with a small and ornate harag in the right margin
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                      <locus target="#138r" facs="138"/>
                      <desc type="Supplication">
                        written in a later, trained hand.
                        <foreign xml:lang="gez">
                          ዝንቱ፡ ዳዊት፡ ዘአጽቀ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ዘወሀባ፡ ለጉልቢ፡ ማርያም፡ ወዘአቡሁ፡ አለቃ፡ ተድላ፡ ወስመ፡ ጥምቀቱ፡ ወልደ፡ ገብርኤል፡ ወእሙ፡ እማሆይ፡ ተሰማሽ፡ ወስመ፡ ጥምቀታ፡
                          አመተ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</foreign>
                          Translation:
                          <q>This Psalter belongs to Atsqa Iyasus who donated it to Gulbi Maryam [church]. His father is Alaqa Tadla, and his baptismal name is Walda Gabri’el. 
                            His mother is Ǝmmahoy Tasamaš, whose baptismal name is Amatta Iyasus. Whoever steals or effaces it is anamethatized by the authority of Peter and Paul, forever and ever, Amen</q>
                            </desc>
                          </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                      <ref type="item" target="#ms_i1.3"/> has the common edition in the base hand, but all of the strophes for the scholars’ edition of the Song of Songs have been added interlinearly
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#139v" facs="140"/>
                    <desc>
                    Scrawls
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
